about-beepass: BeePass is a free, simple and secure VPN built on top of Outline, an open source project created by JigSaw. Designed with your privacy in mind, BeePass VPN will help you bypass internet censorship and improve your privacy online. BeePass is powered by Shadowsocks and soon will support other protocols.
auto-connect-dialog-detail: Unless you disconnect from your BeePass server, BeePass will automatically connect next time you restart your device.
beepass-plugin-error-admin-permissions: BeePass needs admin permissions in order to run. If you don't have admin permissions, please try again after restarting your Windows computer or ask your system administrator for help.
beepass-plugin-error-antivirus: It seems like your antivirus software is preventing us from successfully connecting.
beepass-plugin-error-invalid-server-cred: It seems like your access key is not valid. If this happens again, please contact your server admin.
beepass-plugin-error-routing-tables: We were not able to configure your routing tables successfully. If this happens again, please reach out to us.
beepass-plugin-error-server-unreachable: We can’t seem to connect to your server. Please check that you are connected to the internet and try again.
beepass-plugin-error-system-configuratio: Sorry, it looks like BeePass is not properly installed. Please try installing it again. If that doesn’t work, please submit feedback through the app.
beepass-plugin-error-udp-forwarding-not-: It seems like this server doesn’t support UDP forwarding. If this happens again, please contact your server admin.
beepass-plugin-error-unsupported-routing: It seems like another VPN is active. Please disconnect it and try again.
beepass-plugin-error-vpn-permission-not-: BeePass needs your permission to set up a VPN connection to the server. Please try again, or submit feedback if you need help.
error-feedback-submission: Sorry, we were unable to submit your feedback. Please check that you are connected to the internet and try again.
error-invalid-access-key: Invalid access key. Please try again, or submit feedback for help.
error-server-incompatible: Sorry, this access key is not compatible with this version of BeePass.
error-timeout: Something seems to be taking longer than expected. Quitting and restarting may help. If this happens again, please submit feedback.
error-unexpected: Sorry, an unexpected error occurred. Quitting and restarting may help. If this happens again, please submit feedback.
error-shadowsocks-unsupported-cipher: The server you requested to add uses an unsafe cipher ({cipher}). Please contact your server admin.
feedback-language-disclaimer: Please note that our team is only able to answer feedback in English.
feedback-privacy: Your feedback, your email address (if provided), and additional information referred to in the {privacyPolicyLinkOpen}Data Collection Policy{privacyPolicyLinkClose} will be sent to the BeePass team. Please do not include personal information in your feedback.
feedback-thanks: Thanks for helping us improve! We love hearing from you.
help-copy:
We are committed to provide a secure and stable service. If you have any questions or need assistance with using BeePass VPN please visit our website or contact us through the following support channels:

Email: Email Support

Telegram: Telegram Support
non-system-vpn-warning-detail: Most browsers connect automatically with BeePass, some do not.
onboarding-slide-1-alt: BeePass is Censorship resistant. BeeBots will help you find our servers but make it harder for those looking to block us.
onboarding-slide-2-alt: BeePass is Secure. Strong encryption protects your communication and browsing.
onboarding-slide-3-alt: Privacy by Design. We maintain the minimal amount of data necessary to provide you with a reliable service.
onboarding-slide-4-alt: Add Your Server and Connect. Use our Email or Telegram bots to get your server and enjoy browsing with a free, unlimited, and secure VPN. Start your journey.
privacy-title: BeePass will never collect your personal information
server-add-instructions: Copy and paste an access key to add a server.
server-add-invalid: {openLine}Invalid access key.{closeLine}Enter a valid access key (ss://) to add a server.
server-create-your-own: Don’t have a VPN server? Get one!
server-create-your-own-zero-state: Don’t have a VPN server? Get one!
server-detected: Please confirm that you want to add this server.
update-downloaded: An updated version of BeePass has been downloaded. It will be installed when you restart BeePass.
